        <updateDate>2025-01-02T21:23:03Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schools Not Shelters Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill denies federal funds to schools providing&amp;nbsp;emergency shelter or housing to certain non-U.S. nationals (&lt;em&gt;aliens &lt;/em&gt;under federal law), subject to exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Under the bill, primary schools, secondary schools, and institutions of higher education are ineligible for federal funds if they provide emergency shelter or housing exclusively to non-U.S. nationals under the order of state, local, or federal government. The bill excepts short-term (72 hours or less) emergency shelter made necessary by qualifying disasters.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Federal funds denied by the bill include grants, loans, loan guarantees, and property, but not certain reimbursements for services rendered.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
